The paper presents a novel method for trademark image retrieval using visual data and hierarchical organization. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for encoding and representing visual data, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on information retrieval and search algorithms suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper's use of natural language processing techniques for text-based image retrieval could place it under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper's use of multimedia data and its evaluation on image databases could also place it under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
